    "body": "### Problem\n\n`bufload` a new buffer then `nvim_set_current_buf` will trigger `BufWinEnter` twice\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\r\n-- test.lua\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"BufWinEnter\", {\r\n\tcallback = function(ev)\r\n\t\tvim.print(ev)\r\n\tend,\r\n})\r\n\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_user_command(\"LoadFile\", function(opts)\r\n\tlocal bufnr = vim.fn.bufadd(opts.fargs[1])\r\n\tvim.fn.bufload(bufnr)\r\n\tvim.api.nvim_set_current_buf(bufnr)\r\nend, { nargs = 1 })\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nnvim --clean -u test.lua\r\n:LoadFile test.lua\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\ntrigger `BufWinEnter` once\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.10.0-dev-2971+g6d732ad3c\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNot try vim\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacos\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
